  Oauth token obtained!

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

datasetid.description: dataset id to retrieve, if not specified all datasets are retrieved

examples:
$ sfdx eai:datasets:vision:create --username myOrg@example.com --pemlocation secrets/einstein.pem
  Oauth token obtained!

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

labels.name: labels
labels.description: Comma-separated list of labels. Maximum number of labels per dataset is 250

name.name: name
name.description: Name of the dataset. Maximum length is 180 characters.

language.name: language
language.description: Dataset language. Optional. Default is N/A. Reserved for future use.

type.name: type
type.description: Type of dataset data. Valid values are image and image-multi-label. Available in Einstein Vision API version 2.0 and later.

path.name: path
path.description: URL of the .zip file. The maximum .zip file size you can upload from a web location is 50 MB.

data.name: data
data.description: URL of the .zip file. The maximum .zip file size you can upload from a web location is 50 MB.

eai:vision:datasets:retrain.description: request to retrain a dataset, optionally with new params

loglevel.name: loglevel
loglevel.description: logging level for this command invocation

modelid.name: modelid
modelid.description: Id of the model to be retrained

epochs.name: epochs
epochs.description: Number of training iterations for the neural network. Optional. Valid values are 1–1,000.

learningrate.name: learningrate
learningrate.description: Specifies how much the gradient affects the optimization of the model at each time step. Optional. Use this parameter to tune your model. Valid values are between 0.0001 and 0.01. If not specified, the default is 0.0001. We recommend keeping this value between 0.0001 and 0.001.    This parameter isn't used when training a detection dataset.

trainparams.name: trainparams
trainparams.description: JSON that contains parameters that specify how the model is created.
